    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 protocol is a standardised, FDA-recognised test method and that multi-laboratory replication (two independent labs, N=11 constructs) provides sufficient confidence in the single-condition results. All three QoIs satisfy both the 10% difference criterion and the E/uval < 1.96 validation metric. The overall credibility evidence supports acceptance of the FEA model for the stated COU.",
